Pod networking/ Kubernetes network.
===================================
1) Each pod  should have seprate ipaddress . (True)

2) Two  pod should be communicate to each on same host. (True)

      PodA---Calico (Bridge network)----POdB

3) Two  pod should be communicate to each other ever they are on different host. (True)

      PodA---Calico---Tunl0 (packet encapsulate)-----Network(Infra)------Tunl0---Calico---PodB

4) Pod should be go out side the cluster Network .  (True)

      PodA--Calico--NAT(Iptables)--Eth0---Router--ISP---Internet


Important Notes:

1) Pod network works  SDN(software define network)/CNI(Container network interface)  concept.
     => SDN provide L3 level features.

2) CNI flavour

  1) Weave
  2) flannel
  3) calico

calico

1) It is software define network which provide L-3 layer networking for kubernetes  pod .
2) It act as L3 layer switch on each kubernetes Nodes.
3) Calico  basically designed based on BGP(Border gateway protocol) protocol.
4) Calico also configured routing for Pod . that is why remote pod they are able to reach.

Installation:

1) Container Mode .

2) during installation  calico has configured one default subnet  192.168.0.0/16  (Pod Network)

